      • getMinerWeight

        public double getMinerWeight​(java.lang.String minerName)
        Retrieves the weight associated with the provided miner name.
        Parameters:
        minerName - The registered miner's name.
        Returns:
        A double in the range [0, 1], 1 if the weight has never been set.
        See Also:
        setMinerWeight(String, double)

      • setMinerWeight

        public SocialGraphMinerCombination setMinerWeight​(java.lang.String minerName,
                                                  double minerWeight)
        Gets a created miner with SocialGraphMinerCombination.getMiner(String) and associates a new weight with it. Miner weight of zero makes the miner not participate in predictions. predictNewInteraction(Context, Node) and SocialGraphMiner.recommendInteractions(Context).
        Parameters:
        minerName - The name of the miner whose weight is set.
        minerWeight - The weight to associate with the miner. Should lie in the range [0,1].
        Returns:
        this miner.
        See Also:
        getMinerWeight(String), SocialGraphMinerCombination.createMiner(String, Class)

      • predictNewInteraction

        public double predictNewInteraction​(eu.h2020.helios_social.core.contextualegonetwork.Context context,
                                    eu.h2020.helios_social.core.contextualegonetwork.Node destinationNode)
        Description copied from class: SocialGraphMiner
        Predicts the weight of performing a SEND interaction between the given context's ego and a destination node within a given context. This method should typically return values in the [0,1] range, where higher values correspond to more likely interactions.
        Specified by:
        predictNewInteraction in class SocialGraphMiner
        Parameters:
        context - The context in which to perform the prediction.
        destinationNode - The destination node of the interaction.
        Returns:
        The weight of performing the interaction (higher values are more likely).
